# Desktop Command Center (Phase 27)

Read **[DESKTOP_COMMAND_CENTER.md](../../DESKTOP_COMMAND_CENTER.md)** before changes to the desktop client, desktop APIs, or session pairing.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Tauri shell, tray, local UI | **Desktop client** (`apps/command-center/`) |
| Pairing UI | **Customer App** (`/app/command-center/connect`) |
| Session RPCs, bundle, quick actions | **Shared** (`lib/desktop/`, `/api/desktop/*`) |
| Business logic | **Aipify Core** — never in the desktop app |

## Rules

1. **One Aipify** — desktop consumes `desktop_get_command_center()` / same tables as web
2. Desktop client is a **thin client** — no duplicated Intelligence, Action, or License logic
3. Authentication via hashed desktop session tokens only — never installation secrets locally
4. Support remote logout and session expiration
5. Plan gate: Business+ for desktop pairing (`capabilities.desktop_client`)
6. Respect quiet hours and notification preferences server-side
7. Tray status: green (healthy) · orange (attention) · red (critical) · grey (offline/paused)
8. Phase 1 OS: **macOS only** — Windows/Linux in later phases
9. Prefer **Tauri** over Electron unless blocked by platform constraints

> The Command Center is another window into Aipify Core — not a separate product.
